---
import Chrome from '@layouts/Chrome.astro';

import geocoding from '@assets/map.svg';
import screen from '@assets/screen.svg';
import search from '@assets/search.svg';
import thumb from '@assets/thumb.svg';

import Button from '@components/Button.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<Chrome>
  <section
    class="bg-hero-topography-secondary-10 shadow-xs border-b border-slate-400 bg-slate-100 p-6 dark:bg-zinc-900"
  >
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h1
        class="mb-0 mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-800 md:text-5xl dark:text-slate-50"
      >
        Data to enrich your <span
          class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400">business</span
        >
      </h1>
      <h2
        class="m-1.5 block text-2xl font-light tracking-tight text-slate-700 md:text-3xl dark:text-slate-200"
      >
        An API to access <span class="font-semibold">Utah</span> geospatial data.
      </h2>
      <p
        class="mt-3 text-base font-normal leading-relaxed tracking-wide text-slate-700 md:text-lg dark:text-slate-200"
      >
        The Utah Geospatial Resource Center (UGRC) is the State of Utah's map
        technology coordination office. The UGRC creates, maintains, and stores
        geospatial data in the State Geographic Information Database (SGID), a
        one-stop shop to hundreds of data layers developed, aggregated, or
        acquired by state government. This web API gives you completely open
        access to
        <span
          class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-400 block text-2xl font-bold tracking-tighter"
        >
          all of that data.</span
        >
      </p>
      <div class="flex justify-center md:my-4">
        <aside
          class="mt-6 flex w-full max-w-xl flex-wrap justify-evenly rounded-lg border border-slate-300 bg-white p-5 sm:items-center md:mb-6 md:mt-10 dark:border-slate-600 dark:bg-slate-800"
        >
          <h2
            class="m-0 text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-2xl sm:leading-6 dark:text-slate-100"
          >
            Ready to dive in?
            <br />
            <span class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-200"
              >Learn everything to start.</span
            >
          </h2>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <div class="mt-4 flex md:mt-0">
              <Button href="/getting-started" text="Get started" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="bg-secondary-800 bg-hero-circuit-board w-full text-white">
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-5">
      <div class="leading-relaxed tracking-wide">
        <h1 class="text-accent-500 col-span-2 text-3xl font-bold lowercase">
          Simple, Spatial
        </h1>
        <p class="ml-3 mt-0 text-lg">
          You can learn so much from a house address once it has been geocoded.
          When you geocode data, you unlock the ability to visualize the data in
          a different way. And you can use our search endpoint to answer endless
          questions about your addresses or location.
        </p>
        <h1
          class="text-accent-500 col-span-2 mt-5 text-3xl font-bold lowercase"
        >
          Trust the data
        </h1>
        <p class="ml-3 mt-0 text-lg">
          UGRC was developed specifically to coordinate Utah-specific data, and
          we've been doing this for 30+ years. Other programs can provide you
          with similar data, but if you're looking for information that
          considers the nuances of Utah, this is it&mdash;we have the most
          comprehensive Utah geospatial data, and we want to share it with you.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="px-6 md:pt-4">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-lg pb-6">
      <div
        class="grid max-w-6xl grid-cols-1 gap-5 text-left font-light leading-relaxed tracking-wide text-slate-600 md:grid-cols-2 dark:text-slate-100"
      >
        <div>
          <h1
            class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300 col-span-2 text-2xl font-normal"
          >
            What is geocoding
          </h1>
          <p class="ml-3 mt-0 text-lg">
            Geocoding allows you to find a geographic location (i.e., the
            geographical coordinates) from an address. UGRC's geocoding
            philosophy is unique in that we would rather give you no match than
            the wrong match. But we assure you: we will have the best match
            rates for Utah addresses.
          </p>
          <p class="ml-3 mt-5 text-lg">
            How can we be so sure?&mdash;Because we're the experts in Utah
            geospatial data.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hidden justify-center self-center md:flex">
          <Image src={geocoding} alt="Map" />
        </div>
        <div class="hidden justify-center self-center md:flex">
          <Image src={search} alt="Search" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1
            class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300 col-span-2 text-2xl font-normal"
          >
            What is searching
          </h1>
          <p class="ml-3 mt-0 text-lg">
            Searching allows you to search through more than{' '}
            <a
              href="https://gis.utah.gov/documentation/sgid/"
              class="font-semibold">1,000,000</a
            > rows of spatial SGID data. With over
            <span class="font-semibold">300</span> layers of real-world data that
            you can run queries against in the SGID, the possibilities can be a little
            overwhelming. But the searching endpoint really opens up the opportunity
            for serious information gathering. You need a way to sift through all
            that information and make sense of it and our search endpoint can help
            you do that.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h1
            class="text-secondary-600 dark:text-secondary-300 col-span-2 text-2xl font-normal"
          >
            Location Matters
          </h1>
          <p class="ml-3 mt-0 text-lg">
            The demand for <span class="font-semibold">geospatial</span> and{
              ' '
            }
            <span class="font-semibold">location</span> based information has increased
            dramatically as many disciplines realize the power of spatial data. A
            customer's address stored in a database has only so many uses. With this
            API, the door opens to many spatial opportunities from <span
              class="font-semibold">visually</span
            >
            seeing customer locations on a map to being able to spatially analyze
            their relationship or patterns in conjunction with other events such as
            disease occurrences, natural disaster affected areas, and other location
            based occurrences.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hidden justify-center self-center md:flex">
          <Image src={screen} alt="a screen" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section
    class="bg-hero-topography-secondary-10 shadow-xs dark:border-primary-800 border-y border-slate-400 p-6"
  >
    <div
      class="mx-auto my-6 mb-16 grid grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-slate-700 md:mb-0 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-9 dark:text-slate-200"
    >
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumb up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Locally sourced data
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Address Reversals
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Delivery Points
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Mileposts
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          P.O. Boxes
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Mapping library integration
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Open License
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          Free
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col">
        <div class="justify-center self-center">
          <Image
            src={thumb}
            alt="a thumbs up"
            class="text-accent-600 mb-3 h-8 w-8"
          />
        </div>
        <div
          class="justify-center self-center text-center text-base font-thin uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          No Restrictions
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Chrome>
